review_text: The reviews here are not accurate and I’m pretty sure they’ve had reviews taken down. review_text: My daughter lives at 828 EDM and the place is covered in black mold.  The management was unresponsive for 3 weeks while the girls contacted them about the situation at their apartment. They finally got a mold mitigation Company to check out the apartment which discovered black mold under the island wall from a leaking dishwasher . (Which management refused to fix at an earlier request by the girls)  they finally agreed to fix the issue. The girls had to move out for a week-so the drywall could be removed to get rid of the mold. It was supposed to be fixed last Friday  so the girls could move in. Today it is Still  not fixed, there is no running water yet management told them they  could move back in as the apartment is “habitable” This condition is totally unacceptable yet management  does not seem to care. The stress on the girls is getting extreme. They just want a good place to live and get back to their studies. It is sad housing is so hard in the IV that property managers don’t take care of their tenants.
owner_answer: Hi Renee Sherman, we can assure you that we do not find this type of behavior acceptable, and we would like to address the situation you have described. We're disappointed to hear of the negative experience you had at our location. If you are willing to give us another chance, please reach out to us at (805) 316-7734 to speak to our manager directly.

name: Hollister Village
review_text: Living here is wonderful. The staff is so responsive to any issues and put so many fun community events together like movie nights, yoga, and pizza parties. Everything is so well maintained and the landscaping is beautiful. I so enjoy being here and am really thankful for all the workers who keep everything so nice.

We are grateful to have you as a resident and look forward to continuing to provide you with an enjoyable living experience. - The Team at Hollister Village

name: Hollister Village
review_text: For what you get it’s over priced. They claim luxury housing when you don’t even have AC or heating. Not to mention a lot of the appliances were last updated in like 2008. Whether that’s gym equipment or the house appliances you get at home. But for the most part it’s a clean place to live in.
owner_answer: We appreciate your thoughts on our pricing and amenities. We apologize for any inconvenience you may have experienced. We strive to provide a clean living environment for our residents and will take your comments into consideration as we continue to improve. - The Team at Hollister Village

name: Hollister Village
review_text: I do not recommend this apartment complex. I pay $3700 for small one bedroom apartment with extremely old washer and dryer models. A few weeks ago I came home and found an enormous amount of ants all over my apartment. I submitted a service request. 3 days later!!!! someone came to spray my apartment, so literally, I had to have ants crawling on me while I was sleeping for 3 days!! Today I woke up and found thousands of ants in my apartment again!! I called to the leasing office in the morning and they explained to me that it is because of the weather change and sent  ME to the store to buy spray and get rid of the ants in the apartment I’m paying almost 4k for. They told me the earliest day someone can come is next Wednesday, so if I don’t want to wait I have to solve this problem by myself. Just think about it. I have to live with ants for the whole week or I have to spend my money and time and learn skills how to basically be a pest control. Btw I am not talking about a few ants. I have literally thousands of them all over my place. And let’s not forget that they can bite and spread diseases. So, do not live in this apartment complex. I experienced one of the worst, health threatening experiences here. And please see the pictures. Also I have 2 dogs and as you can see ants are inside of my dogs’ bowls all over their food. So I have to throw away $100 bag of dog food and food from all my kitchen cabinets, and, once again, I have to go to the store, spend money on chemicals and spray my apartment….
owner_answer: Thank you for bringing this issue to our attention, Katerina. We apologize for any inconvenience you have experienced with the ants in your apartment. Our team is committed to addressing maintenance concerns promptly, and we regret that there was a delay in resolving this issue. We understand that living with ants can be frustrating and we appreciate your patience. We have taken note of your feedback and will work towards improving our response time in the future. Please feel free to reach out to our leasing office if you have any further concerns. -The Team at Hollister Village

name: Hollister Village
review_text: Horrible , stay away it’s turning into little Isla Vista , new BBQ grills are needed since forever , no upkeep and lack of community. Residents events are cheap, other communities have some great resident events and even get it catered !! for what we are paying this is a joke . Beautiful on the outside but only leased because of lack of housing the area.
owner_answer: Hi there. Please note that our grills have been delivered and we look forward to installing them as soon as possible! As for your other concerns, we are unable to identify you as a resident, due to the anonymity of this review. Please stop by our office so we properly can address these claims in the most efficient way possible. Thank you and we hope to hear from you promptly. -The Team at Hollister Village

review_text:
Where do I begin?
First off thank you to Mars for making this such an incredible and peaceful move in. The apartment complex is beautiful, plenty of shops around and very convently located. He’s helped a lot and we can’t thank him enough!
Talk about location! Close to a private beach, feeling seculed and peaceful in a safe environment. Plenty of amazing food within a quater mile of walking, this is the best apartment I’ve ever lived in. If something happens like a lightbulb goes out they are very good with communication and helping figure out our new home! Thank you to Chris as well for all the help.

Thank you again for choosing Hollister Village as your home, and we look forward to continuing to exceed your expectations! -The Team at Hollister Village

review_text: Beautiful property with super courteous and helpful employees. Mars, Chris, and Kristen were all so welcoming and gracious, and made us feel right at home. Would highly recommend this property and awesome team to anyone looking to move into the area.

review_text:
Update: Hi Hollister Village, I’m adding this update here because it’s been 10 days since you posted the reply to my review below. I’ve been checking my email, voicemail, snail mail and bank account…. I haven’t received any sort of reimbursement or direct communication from you that I’m aware of. Please let me know if you’ll actually be issuing a reimbursement.

Caroline

Warning about move-out/cleaning fees: I lived here for 1 year and kept the apartment in perfect condition. Before moving out I deep cleaned the apartment checking off every item on the suggested cleaning list to try and avoid being charged a cleaning fee. I left the apartment cleaner than I received it. I was charged $600+ for unit cleaning + carpet cleaning + painting. I wanted clarification on the charge and exactly what they believed was dirty. I spent weeks being bounced around on the phone between Hollister/Lyon Living/Central Billing. They could NOT provide an itemized list of what was dirty and required a full unit cleaning.

I finally gave up and paid the $674 cleaning bill because I can’t deal with them anymore.

Very disappointed with the move-out cleaning bill experience.
owner_answer: Hi, Caroline. We are sorry to see that your living experience has resulted in a negative assessment of our community. After further review, we have decided to discount the cleaning due to the inconvenience caused. We will also send an updated final account statement. name: Hollister Village
review_text:
Hollister Village apartments is a great place to live. There is ample parking, washer and dryer in units, in walking distance to many restaurants, grocery stores, pet stores. Neighbors are friendly especially the ones with dogs. The head office staff have made every effort to keep amenities available
The head office staff are accommodating and helpful. The staff are personable and are here to assist with any problem. Ground staff are friendly are helpful if there any issues.

name: Hollister Village
review_text: It has been a very difficult experience looking for an apartment in Santa Barbara area for the past few months until I finally got a hold of Bobbie Bush from Hollister Village Apartments. He provided our family with an impeccable customer service! We've waited few months to finally get a place in Hollister Village Apartments and from the first phone call to Bobbie he was nothing but amazing. He is very polite on the phone, gives you all the information you need and the thing I love the most is that he listens. This kind of customer service will set Hollister Village apart from all other places, not to mention the beautiful property. Thank you again Bobbie for all your help! I'd highly recommend this place and Bobbie to work with. He will exceed your expectations!

Hollister Village

name: Hollister Village
review_text: This place is really very lovely.  There is a lot of storage (hall closet, pantry, walk-in closet in bedroom, patio closet), the appliances are stainless steel and look great.  They have the lights that hang down over the bar and many of the lights are adjustable.  They have fans that are also adjustable using the light switch on the wall.  The bathtub is deep.  I have had no issues so I have had no reason to contact management so I am not sure about their response rate.  I use the gym (which is small, but has everything you need), the pool , and the spa.  There is a large space with a bar where you can cook and have parties and I have seen some people doing just that.  It is pretty quiet all the time, but you can hear the train on occasion when it goes past.  They have free electric vehicle charging and assigned parking with plenty of additional parking for guests.  I have never struggled to find a spot.  The only downside is that it is very expensive and there is no central air conditioning, only heat!  It has gotten up to 80 degrees indoors this summer and we have not made it to the hottest month of the year yet.  So invest in a really good fan!
owner_answer: Brittany, thank you so much for the kinds words. We really appreciate you. Please let us know if you need anything at all.

name: Hollister Village
review_text: My husband and I have lived here for 2 years and we absolutely LOVE living here!! For me, the kitchen is the best feature. I do a lot of cooking and I cannot rave enough about the counter space! It's also very rewarding to have a washer and dryer in its own space (in the corner of the hallway), the washer and dryer is not very loud at all. The bathrooms are spacious as well, although the bathtub is very deep, so be careful.  Definitely take advantage of the computer room (3 computers plus free unlimited printing) game room, gym, pool, and Jacuzzi-Everything is always SPOTLESS CLEAN!! Which is very hard to find at other apartment complexes. In addition- the staff/management here are always available! I have never had an issue when something needs to be fixed (and yes I have put in several maintenance requests) because they have always fixed the issue as quick as they could. My husband says the staff alone is worth paying the extra bucks because of how well they keep this apartment complex clean and making you feel like your'e apart of the community here :)
owner_answer: Karisa, thank you so much for the five stars! We appreciate you and your husband, and we're glad that you're enjoying your time here at Hollister Village. If you need anything at all, please don't hesitate to reach out!

name: Hollister Village
review_text: Lived here for 3 years, had 0 problems. Rod and the team at leasing office are extremely helpful with everything from leasing to renewal of leases and all our requests! The service staff is excellent, all of our service requests always used to get processed quickly. The community is clean with a lot of friendly people around and the apartments are awesome! Lots of space with high end appliances. I highly recommend checking Hollister Village out if you are in the Goleta area!
owner_answer: Sumanth, thank you so much for the 5 stars! If you need anything at all, don't hesitate to reach out.

review_text: We love to live here. Everyone is friendly and professional. Especially thanks Evelyn, she helps us from start till end. Very patient and she is so nice that even my two kids love her. Also thanks Emilio for his hard work to fix our apt issues ASAP. We really appreciate. I highly recommend this place, it is also near Costco, Smart&final and Girsh Park.

name: Hollister Village
review_text: Customer Service to get approved for rent a new condo is excellent. The agent is outstanding. That is all. The condo was not ready to be rented, the guest bathroom has, and I say, has because it is with the shower faucet broken before I moved in with my family, and it is still broken. Maintenance team of two people supposed to fix it, we used one day, and it got broken again, I sent the request to be repair in the same day, it is time that no one show up, or ask what is going on, or replace the faucet, which by the way is too cheap, you can find it in the 99 cents store. I tried to speak with the Village director, it was Mission Impossible, it could be easier to speak with the director of my department. I just signed the lease for 11 months, and I would need to wait almost the 11 months because it has not been even a week that I move in. Ooohh Nooo!!

review_text: Great location and the pool was amazing. Rod, Chad, Evelyn and the maintainable team have been great and went above and beyond to help my parents when they came down for a visit. Love living here with our little one.

name: Hollister Village
review_text: Worst experience ever. They charged us 3800 bucks for deposit while we provided the docs they asked for(proof of income). I live in LA and my bf lives there. I have a dog, which stays with me most of the time and I bring it with me to visit my bf, like probably once in two weeks, and the leasing office was trying so hard to make us pay the 1000 bucks for a dog deposit. They really made me feel like all they care about is money money and money. Of course we ignored it, and then they emailed us, threatened our roommates “if you don’t pay the dog deposit, you will be kicked out”. So we paid for it. And then I decided I’m just never gonna come to this community any more, so I asked my bf to take back the check( at that time I was visiting with my dog but I’ll be back in 2 days), and the woman in the office said that “you either signed the document or you gotta send the dog away RIGHT NOW”. almost forgot to mention that they are so good at asking for money but have not given us the garage keys or the other gym key since my bfs moved in for 1 month:)

review_text: Was just told by maintenance that these apartments do not have AC, I did not know that because of course I check the thermostat and it says it has Cooling, dogs barking all day, maintenance does not respond appropriately, I cannot wait to break this lease which I will try to do in the next few weeks

If there is a problem with barking dogs, I can gladly address that as well. 90% of the homes and apartments in this area do not have A/C because we are so close to the ocean, not to mention we do not advertise that we have A/C.  Our thermostats have the capability to do both heating and cooling, however there are no A/C’s connected for that feature to work. Again, we are here to help and I would really like the opportunity to discuss these concerns with you. We have a few Morgan’s in our system and I was not able to discern which entry was you and what your contact information. Please reach out to me at hollistervillage@lyonliving.com or at 805-284-9615 so that we can touchbase. Looking forward to hearing from you!

name: Willow Springs Apartments
review_text:
My family and I had to move from the place we called home for 14 years. I heard about Willow Springs and immediately contacted them. Shawn is AMAZING he walked me through the whole process, excellent communication and positive attitude. He really demonstrates he cares about the applicants/tenants. Our apartment looked brand new, clean and our moving process was excellent. Very organized.
The community is clean and the neighbors are respectful and friendly .I’m very happy to call willow springs our new home!  They truly care about their tenants.

If there is anything else we can do for you at this time, please don’t hesitate to reach out. We hope you have a great day!

name: Willow Springs Apartments
review_text: I work at UCSB and I chose Willow Springs because of their competitive pricing and proximity to campus. After living there for two years, my rent increased by $500 per month and they charged me $750 for a year worth of renting a laundry machine (for the previous year) because they "forgot" to add the charge to my lease. Please note that this unknown charge also happened to other reviewers listed here. I will be moving out this year because I cannot afford the apartment anymore, nor can I trust management.
owner_answer:
Hello, Kristy,

Thank you for your review. We are very sorry that you had anything less than a positive experience here at Willow Springs. Our team strives to exceed the expectations of our community; your feedback enables us to provide the best experience possible. Our team has investigated the areas of concerns that you have mentioned within your review and will be reaching out to you directly to further to address, in a prompt and accurate manner. Thank you again for your feedback.

Warm Regards.

name: Willow Springs Apartments
review_text: I have been living here for 3 years. From the beginning, everything seemed fine, but in the last year, it all went downhill with the management. Rude people, having a complete mess in their paperwork (they let us know 2 months after lease renewal that there is a problem in our contract and therefore we had to pay more for rent then we agreed to + then they sent us a lease agreement of different people in the apartment complex). All the capable people that used to be in the office left and now it is just a total mess of rude and irresponsible people who are not even able to do a simple lease renewal with you. (and will share your personal data with other people in the complex). Rather avoid this place if you can - we will for sure leave as soon as we can.
owner_answer: Miroslava, thank you for taking some time to give us this feedback regarding our community. Our team values our residents’ input and appreciate that you returned our call yesterday to discuss your lease renewal process questions. We are happy that you have chosen Willow Springs as your home for the last three years and that you have decided to renew your lease in 2021. Our team always strives for excellent customer service and attention to detail, and we hope that we provided you with the information you needed. Please reach out to us directly at (805) 968-3300 if you have anything else you would like to discuss. We are always here to help, and we hope you have a wonderful day.

name: Willow Springs Apartments
review_text: Our short time at Willow Springs was incredible and heart-warming. We were in a very tough situation where, without prior awareness, we had to vacate our condo in the Bay Area very quickly and needed a short term rental in Santa Barbara & Goleta. We found the most welcoming landing from the team at Willow Springs. From Kevin Hammer's support remotely, Shawn Douglas' warm welcome and support throughout, to Dan and Aaron's quick fixes and attention to detail when issues arose, to the rest of the incredible team at Willow Springs, our stay could not have been better, especially during a difficult time for our family: moving quickly during a pandemic with an eight months pregnant wife. Willow Springs, from top to bottom treats their residences with integrity and hospitality. Issues were handled timely and fairly, and everything was over-communicated. I wish we could have had more time there, if nothing else for the warm people and lovely grounds. I couldn't recommend them more.
owner_answer: Greg, thank you so much for your 5-star rating and review of Willow Springs Apartments. We are so happy to hear about your experience staying with us and the help and service you received from our team. We’re glad you were able to call our community your home for a while and wish you the best in your future adventures! Thank you again and have a great day!

name: Willow Springs Apartments
review_text: used to be a nice place to live but i've gotten over it. airport right across the street. sometimes the planes come and go, sometimes its back to back. the management really cares about how the place look. gotta keep your patio clean, can't back in your vehicle (even though its safer), water the plants every night during the drought, limit of 3 people with you at the pool. some of the management is nice and will smile when passing by. others will just ignore you or pretend you're not there. they don't do anything about people speeding through the complex. they don't do anything about people littering their cigarette butts on the ground. they don't do anything about abandoned vehicles, and theres no designated spot for motorcycles to share. plus rent increases are always fun

name: Willow Springs Apartments
review_text: Worst management and maintenance ever. I do not know why those stupid arrogant agents still have their jobs. Do not dream about one day items in your apartment that need to be fixed will be fixed by the maintenance services. Even if you ask the office to do it, they still will ignore your request anyway and shift the blame to others. So I just suggest if anything in your apartment needs to be fixed, you better hope they can be fixed by themselves.

name: Willow Springs Apartments
review_text: Been living here for over 10 months and I really love the community and the staff in the Leasing Office. They were always accommodating the couple times that I reached out to them. My only gripe is that I wish that some of the residents in the community would be more courteous to their fellow neighbors.

name: Willow Springs Apartments
review_text: I love living here! The staff is responsive and kind. The pool, hot tubs, outdoor fire place, barbecues, walking trail, exercise stations and gym are great. The apartments are spacious and offer lots of storage.

name: Willow Springs Apartments
review_text:
Lived here for a short amount of time and I'm glad. The management is THE WORST you will find in any sort of residential housing area in or around the Santa Barbara area.

If you are a young professional trying to make ends meet I'm sure this looks like an appealing place to live. DO NOT BE FOOLED. The management is bureaucratic and will literally NITPICK at every little thing whether it be something of yours in your own backyard to threatening to tow your car because you haven't put the new tags on it yet ( Between the time I paid for new stickers and got them I was on my "last notice" before they said I could expect to find my only means of transportation to support my livelihood at some tow yard on MY dime.

Go figure this though, when I ask for someone to come repair the rotting wood on my backyard fence they made me wait a month and when they FINALLY got around to it it was like pulling teeth...

These people are inconsiderate. These people are rude. These people are idiots. Keep your money, keep your sanity, and keep the hell away from this apartment complex.

name: Willow Springs Apartments
review_text: Like much of Goleta, incredibly expensive. INCREDIBLY. Yes. There's a pool. No, no air conditioner. Things I wish I'd known before I moved to the Santa Barbara area.

name: Willow Springs Apartments

name: DEL PLAYA APARTMENTS
review_text: So happy I got to finish my senior year living on such an amazing property, if we weren't graduating we would've stayed another year! name: DEL PLAYA APARTMENTS
review_text: I could not ask for a better place to have spent my year! Shawn was the best landlord I’ve ever had. The location is so convenient! It is so close to UCSB, the beach, and all the shops and eating places! I would live here again in a heartbeat. We had a really nice space and got compliments every time someone would visit. The front yard is huge and super nice for gatherings and just hanging out! Had the best year, 10/10 would recommend!!!!!!:)

name: DEL PLAYA APARTMENTS
review_text: Just finished my year lease at 6508, and it was a phenomenal place to live. Not only is the front yard beautiful, with lots of outdoor features, but Shawn is a great landlord. It was really easy to communicate any problems we ran into, and I’m definitely going to miss living at this lovely place close to both the beach and campus.

name: DEL PLAYA APARTMENTS

name: DEL PLAYA APARTMENTS

review_text: Loved this property! Me and 7 of my buddies lived here for a year and couldn’t have enjoyed it more. The location is amazing and the house comes with many outdoor amenities that adds to the value. Surrounded by lush greenery, this property allows its tenants privacy from the busy commotion of the del Playa drive while simultaneously being apart of the UCSB community. With the recently added turf to the front yard, 6508 is the place to be. The landlord is incredibly responsive, attentive, and respectful to the tenants as well.

name: DEL PLAYA APARTMENTS
review_text: Living here was amazing! The other tenants made it a fun experience for me and to top it off it is super close to campus. The landlord is really nice and is always accessible. Any time something broke, the landlord made sure to have it fixed immediately. I really recommend applying here, it is the perfect place.

name: DEL PLAYA APARTMENTS
review_text: I lived here last year and it was an amazing way to end my time in Isla Vista. Shawn was always ready to help and answer any of our questions. I would 10/10 live here again.

name: The Tahitian Apartments
review_text: Great location on El Colegio with close proximity to a bus stop. Our experience with the apartment was a good one. We had this apartment for 4 years. We have seen multiple tenant managers during this time. The current management under the able leadership of Dustyn Peiffer is excellent. They have all been very responsive and helpful. I would highly recommend The Tahitian.

name: The Tahitian Apartments
review_text:
1. The manager entered my apartment without permission while I was in my shower. He knocked, waited about 30 seconds (not an over exaggeration) and entered my home and said he needed to do maintenance.

2. They will not give your security deposit back. We have called and sent emails and they were ignoring all of them. So we had to go to them in person. Where they gave us only a small portion of it back so they can’t “paint and clean” We have never thrown a party or had guests over.

3. There is constant work being done. Everyday. They were repainting the roof, and had a sign out that said that they weren’t responsible for paint on cars. But, by the time I went out to see this, my black vehicle was covered in white paint specks to this day. Other people had to cover their vehicles to avoid the paint.

Overall, the apartment is nice. But the management will try their hardest not to give your deposit back, potentially enter your apartment at random moments and there is constant work being done, water shutting off almost every week it seems and loud equipment being used early in the morning constantly.

name: The Tahitian Apartments
review_text: I moved out in September after two years living here. Its going to be hard to live in another apartment but relocation called me away.  The apartment was amazing. The staff was superb. Things were addressed quickly and professionally. I will miss it there for sure.

name: The Tahitian Apartments
review_text: I would give them 0 starts if I could. First of all, our fridge was broken for 21 days (Sep 28 to Oct 19). We had over $600 worth of food that went bad because of that. They did not reimburse us for any of it and additionally we had to spend so much money on take out for 3 weeks straight. They do not respond to any of our messages and they keep on stalling by saying they are talking to "corporate". They took 72% of our security deposit. Saying they took 18 hours and 6 gallons of paint ("costing them $830.28). Also $122.99 for fixing a $12.99 part (saying it took them 2 hours to fix). Lastly they say it costs $323 for cleaning the apartment when they left when they originally said it would cost only $250. I would not recommend living here if you want your security deposit back.

name: The Tahitian Apartments
review_text:
DON’T LIVE HERE

I lived here for a year and the apartment complex is horrible. We’ve had to deal with cockroaches, crickets, ant infestations, sewage leaks, clogged sinks, among other things with little to no response from the leasing office.

One of the tenants had to move out last year due to alleged asbestos in the bedroom.

If you’d like a functioning apartment with management that responds, I’d recommend you look somewhere else.

name: The Tahitian Apartments
review_text:
DO NOT STAY AT THIS PLACE IF YOU CARE ABOUT YOUR WELL-BEING! I lived at the wave for 2 years and in that time, we have been infested with cockroaches, crickets, and pincher bugs, all of which took weeks of requesting service to get taken care of. We have had to deal with clogged sinks and showers, which as well took well over a month to be delt with. The service is slow and I am not a lawyer but they have done things I would be surprised to learned weren’t illegal. (Changing the terms of the lease agreement, neglecting carbon monoxide alarms etc.) The service is inexcusable and from the bottom of my heart I have nothing good to say about this place other than the amazing neighbors I have been able to bond with though shared hardships of living in this place.

What really set me over the edge is seeing my neighbors closet fill with sewage water due to inadequate plumbing and ruin their clothing and belongings. This place is horrendous.

name: The Tahitian Apartments
review_text: My girlfriend & I moved here from Pennsylvania & our experience so far has been nothing but pleasant. All of our neighbors have been so welcoming & friendly from the moment we walked in. Every single staff member we’ve interacted with have been just as welcoming & helpful, especially Brian, who has been our go-to guy ever since we started on our apartment search. We had some small discrepancies with the locks & blinds in our bedroom, but Carlos the maintenance guy came in & fixed it within the day. Overall, we have been extremely satisfied with our experience & would highly recommend the Tahitian apartments to anyone looking to move to Santa Barbra.

name: The Tahitian Apartments

Great apartment management and amenities.
BBQing in the  pool area is a great escape to daily responsibilities and to hangout with friends.
Ana and Carlos are always available to help with any questions or problems and building upkeep is great!!

Totally recommended to get your money's worth  .

name: The Loop Apartments
review_text: This is my first year living at The Loop apartment complex, so far it has been a great experience. Both the Leasing Team and Maintenance have been super quick with getting questions and or maintenance requests answered/fixed. One of the main contacts for the leasing team has been Ana and she has gone above an beyond to make me feel welcome and valued as a tenant. Luis does such a good job and is super quick to help once maintenance requests are made. Overall, the community within The Loop apartment complex is great to be apart of and I'm super glad to be able to renew my lease and prolong my stay at The Loop.
owner_answer:
Rubi,

Thanks so much for sharing your experience with us and your 4 star review. Our team is happy to see you enjoyed visiting our community and we hope our staff made your decision to lease with us that much easier! We can't wait to hear from you again soon.

name: The Loop Apartments
review_text: The tour was informative and Ana was great at answering all questions we had.  Sadly, we were not able to see an “actual” apartment but were directed to the website for details about floor plans and pricing but having an actual suite to see while there would’ve been really helpful.  Ana seemed to be friendly and appreciated by the residents we encountered while touring the property which made it seem like she is a “good adult presence” for the students living there.  I would suggest working toward having a list of students’ units available with advanced tour notice so that prospective students can get a better idea of the finishes and furniture inside the suites.  Regarding the students’ privacy, I think there are many ways to provide incentives to the one or two units’ occupants that would make this an option for possible future residents.  The details of the living space are hard to get a feel for from a “floor plan” simulation on the website.
owner_answer:
Michele,

We are so appreciative of your 4 star review and for taking the time to share it with us. At The Loop, our goal is to provide residents with the highest quality experiences. We hope you have a great day!

name: The Loop Apartments
review_text: Hi! When my roommates and I started looking for apartments, we chose the Loop because of its great location, and that it came furnished. However, what made us love living here and want to continue to live in this apartment complex, is the community that is built here. This includes the frequent community events that are held, or just seeing friendly staff that are here to help. For me Ana from the Leasing Team and Luis from maintenance have worked so hard not only to respond to any issues I had asap but they make sure that everybody living here feels welcomed and cared for.
owner_answer:

review_text: I’ve had a great experience at the loop! A current resident for 2 years now. The staff is always super responsive to any maintenance requests or questions that I may have. Any request I have gets responded to very quickly. The building always has a staff member out front in the lobby so it always feels secure. Definitely an upgrade from past experiences in IV.

name: The Loop Apartments
review_text: Living at the loop was a disappointment. The microwave was broken when we got there. We submitted multiple maintenance requests to fix it yet it never got fixed and I’m guessing that will be taken out of my security deposit too. The contract said I would be getting my security deposit within 21 days of my lease ending and it’s been 30 and I still haven’t received it. One of the laundry machines did not work for nearly the entire year until they started doing tours for upcoming residents, also with how much we pay, the laundry should cost less or nothing at all. The elevator and wifi would stop working so often to the point where I would specifically do tests and homework elsewhere on rainy or windy days because I knew it wouldn’t work. The front desk workers were rarely at the desk and didn’t seem to take anything seriously. One of my packages got stolen because they weren’t doing their job and they never did anything about it. It’s completely overpriced and definitely not worth it.
owner_answer: We apologize for your negative experience with us at Copper Social. We hope to provide a better experience for all of our residents and would like to discuss any feedback as it helps us get better. Please reach out to us at leasing@theloopiv.com. Thank you!

name: The Loop Apartments
review_text:
Lived here for just under a year. Although Cardinal Group management is less bad than some other Isla Vista property management companies, my overall impression was nonetheless awful. I’d summarize my experience here as unprofessional, taxing, and poorly staffed.

On the other hand, it looks pretty from the outside, and the location and view are unbeatable.   If those positives are worth it, just come with your expectations tempered.

 There’s nothing better than hearing our The Loop residents’ positive feedback! Thanks for sharing your experience with us.

name: The Loop Apartments
review_text: Just moved in and I love this place! Great staff and so close to the beach! The Loop is in walking distance from everywhere and has such great views! 10/10 recommend!
owner_answer: Thank you, Ali! We love hearing that you enjoy living with us, and we love that you are here at The Loop!!

name: The Loop Apartments
review_text: The Loop is one of the most overpriced apartment complexes in all of IV for what it’s worth. I think the Cardinal Group has done a terrible job with making sure staff has all the right resources to keep up with its flaws. All the equipment in the gym were rusted over or had cracks/chips in protective coating. Machines did not work due to ocean air exposure and corrosion. The elevator license is more than two years out dated and always broken yet the complex expects the world of their SINGLE handyman who has done all he can to maintain the building by himself to the best of their ability. I feel comfortable giving two stars because the staff has always been nothing but helpful and flexible with all matters at all times. That being said, major renovations are expected especially since rooms are stuffy, dusty, crammed, and small with no circulation or minimal amounts of windows. I’m glad they started with the laundry rooms since they were completely outdated and constantly broken. I hope the management continues to invest in this property since the potential is there. Additionally, having a parking spot should not be an additional $200 monthly add on when rent already ranges from $1,000-$1346.47+ a month.
owner_answer:
Hello, Sarah  We apologize for the inconvenience you may have experienced at our community. Your feedback has been shared with our team and we will address your issues as soon as possible. Thank you for sharing this with our team.

The Loop

review_text: Overall great place to live. Perfect location for everything IV and UCSB. Access to bus system is in close proximity. Security is pretty sound compared to the houses in IV, and the fob system is pretty convenient. Some criticisms would be that the gym equipment is outdated, and needs to be replaced. Management is very kind and the maintenance guy does a great job.

name: The Loop Apartments
review_text: This apartment building itself is okay and better than most in Isla Vista. However, the roommate matching system is very problematic. You'll be assigned with a random person and have no way to resolve any issues. If things don't work out, there's nothing the management can do. My assigned roommate was horrible and I had no choice but to transfer my lease to somebody else. Worst of all, I didn't get my security deposit back as promised.
owner_answer:

We are so sorry that your roommate matching experience was not up to par. We would love to work with you to remedy any issues that you are experiencing as well as discuss any transfer options we may have available. Please contact our leasing team at leasing@theloopiv.com.

The Loop

name: The Loop Apartments
review_text: Loved the rooftop events and staff was friendly. Maintenance guy was very cool. The apartment itself is made of lower quality materials. For example peeling cabinets, cement flooring. Walls are very thin and no AC. Liked the furniture. My room came w a stand alone closet, a desk, a chair, and a bed. Room dividers are made w a 7ft wooden fence, 10ft ceilings. So there’s a bit of a gap. Overall I really liked this place. The location is great. I’ve heard of people getting their bikes stolen from the loop bike racks so maybe don’t leave it there. Free paddle boards to rent. Most students are SBCC. Not many bugs except the occasional spider and flies if you leave the door open too long. Rent increased substantially for next years renters.
owner_answer:
Thank you so much for your review, Natalie. We really appreciate you taking the time out to share your experience with us.

The Loop

name: The Loop Apartments
review_text:
Take every positive review with a grain of salt, as they give residents gift cards for leaving reviews. The Loop is overpriced and management is awful and completely apathetic. I lived there for two years, and in that time we have dealt with multiple floods from floors above, resulting in our walls and ceiling being opened up multiple times and our items getting damaged. The elevator frequently breaks, and people have been stuck unable to open the doors. Theft is common, we have had clothing stolen from the laundry room multiple times, and even items off of our door decorations, and a friend of mine had his speaker stolen. When I reported the thefts, they said there was nothing they could do about the clothing, as there are no cameras in the laundry room, and that they couldn't tell us who stole our door decorations (EVEN THOUGH THEY KNEW WHO IT WAS) because they didn't want to start issues between residents. They forced a new tenant into our room during the pandemic, even though my roommate was high risk (this new tenant made it clear she was unwilling to follow covid protocol, and management upon learning this essentially told us the only thing we could do to prevent them from moving her in was to pay an extra $1420/month in addition to the combined $3000/month we were already paying).
I will say that Luis, who is in charge of maintenance, is awesome. He's friendly, and is quick to take care of maintenance requests. The roof is also great. Just don't move in expecting any kind of respect from management, because they make it abundantly clear that all they want is your money and they do not care about the resident's well-being. We have been lied to by the building's manager multiple times, and they very clearly try to take advantage of college kids who do not know better.
Other things to be aware of, parking spots are limited and go quickly, and cost $200/month, and do not fit longer cars. There is also a $200/month fee for pets. Laundry costs around $1.50 per wash and about the same per drying cycle, but count on at least one washing machine and one dryer being broken, and having to dry your clothes twice as the dryers are not very powerful.
owner_answer: Natalie, thank you for your feedback. It is our goal is to provide the best possible service and we are truly sorry that your experience was less than satisfactory.  Our team would be happy to speak with you and resolve the issues you are having. Please contact our Leasing Office at (805)328-5007 at your earliest convenience.

name: The Loop Apartments
review_text:
After moving in to The Loop, I have had experiences with a drain of my shower in the Cali Suite being very slow, things weren't as clean as I had hoped as well. However, after speaking with the manager and Luis, it appears that they try to take comments very seriously and are very helpful when it comes to things that concern a resident. As this is my first time renting an apartment, the process seemed seemless and very easy to go through. The only complaint I have is I wished that many of the things in the apartment were fixed the moment you walk in. Also, they don't tell you about a couch that doesn't come with a partially furnished apartment so I am glad that Elizabeth took care of the request to have a couch in the apartment when I asked.

Thanks for taking care of me and the apartments in the building! I know its demanding, but it has to be done and I'm glad it's trying to be done.
owner_answer: Hi Anna, thank you for leaving this detailed feedback about your experience with The Loop. Thank you very much for sharing these comments. Let us know if there is anything else we can assist with!

name: The Loop Apartments
review_text: Not one to leave reviews but had to after seeing the rooftop at this place. I toured 4 places in IV and this place sold me because of the view and the quality of my tour - manager walked by and introduced herself and asked about us which was actually really nice. Prices are reasonable when you look at everywhere else that offers housing but the location is better because you’re closer to campus, beach and you get better views from rooms.

name: The Loop Apartments
review_text: If I could give the Loop zero stars I would, living at the Loop was an absolutely horrible and scarring experience. I don't even know where to begin with all the things that went wrong... to start our door was broken right from the start of moving in and we reported it right away, the staff said no problem they can get it fixed within the next couple of days but didn't actually end up fixing the door until the week of moving out (almost a year later). With this door not being able to lock we had many creeps just walk right on into our place, one time being a homeless man coming into our place in the middle of the night and me waking up the next morning to him asleep on the ground right next to my bed. This places water heater and laundry machines would continuously break as well resulting in freezing cold showers weekly and no clean clothes. This apartment complex is a very dirty and unmaintained place to live especially considering the rent is so expensive just to live in a shoebox. Don't even bother paying extra for a parking spot too because someone will park in your spot anyways and the staff won't do anything about it.
owner_answer:
Hello Summer,

Thank you for providing this feedback to our team. We apologize that your experience was not one that is representative of what we want for our residents and we will ensure issues like this do not occur again. Thank you.

The Loop

name: The Loop Apartments
review_text: My daughter just moved out after a 1-year lease.  The apartment itself was okay.  The bathroom floor was nasty and in my opinion they did a poor thing cleaning the apartment before we moved in.  There were numerous little things here and there but I figured it's not a new building so told my daughter to deal with them.  The worst experience was toward the end of the lease.  My daughter was in a triple loft with 2 other girls in an open space on the loft.  Both of these 2 girls sub-leased their bed spaces to others for the months of June and July.  One of them turned out to be a BOY.  I was shocked when I found out that The Loop knew and allowed that to happen.  Needless to say I moved my daughter out the day the boy moved in.  So my daughter didn't even lived there for 2 months while I was stuck paying for the rent.  If The Loop management is reading this,  I'd like to request refund for the 2 months that the boy was there.  Also, this boy decided that since my daughter moved out all the spaces belong to him.  So when we turned in the keys early July, the front desk girl couldn't even complete a final walk thru to check us out since there was junks all over my daughter's desk, bed and closet which all belong to the boy.  This whole situation is absolutely ridiculous and unacceptable.  I'd say get a place somewhere else if you can.

name: The Loop Apartments
review_text: The Loop was a tremendous place to live during my enrollment at UCSB. The employees are extremely nice, welcoming, and always willing to lend a helping hand for any questions or requests that I had. The sky deck really can't be compared to any other apartment complex in the area as it offers tremendous views of sunsets, the beach, and Isla Vista. The deck offers tables to eat, lounging chairs to study in, and a gym. If I were to attend UCSB for an extra year, I would have most definitely lived at The Loop again.
owner_answer: Thank you,Kyle! We love hearing that you enjoy living with us, and we love that you are here at The Loop!!

name: The Loop Apartments
review_text: The Loop is one of the best places to live in IV. The Building complex itself is very modern and cool. There's a Gym on the room with an awesome view of the ocean, it's a great place to relax or hangout. The building is very safe, you need a special key card to get into the building and your room. The hallways are usually quiet, the hallways are cool because each level has a different color/theme, which is unique.  All the workers here are very friendly and helpful, they always say hello when I pass in the lobby (Plus they play the best music in the lobby)  and sometimes give out food and gifts. Theres also a security guard on the weekends who is very friendly. Management is very helpful with everything. My apartment itself is really nice and clean, has kitchen appliances, storage space, and is spacious. Plus its right around all the food in IV and 5 min walk from the beach, enjoyed living here :)
owner_answer: Thank you, Lauren!

name: The Loop Apartments
review_text: I really don't recommend living at The Loop. The pictures are a very misleading representation of what the apartments actually look like. The floor is scuffed concrete, and they don't clean anything before you move in. The apartment was just so uncomfortably dirty. The rent is also unreasonable and very overpriced. If you look elsewhere in Isla Vista, you'll realize that paying above $1000 for a triple, especially with the condition of the apartment, is not worth it at all. Furthermore, I had a terrible situation with my assigned roommates in both of the apartments I lived in (I moved out of the first one because I struggled with one of my roommates, only to end up in another awful situation). The Loop's cleanliness, rent, and roommate-matching need a lot of improvement.
owner_answer: Hello, we are sorry to hear The Loop did not meet your expectations. We strive to offer the best experience for our residents. We would be happy to discuss this with you in detail. If you can email info@theloopiv.com, that would be great

name: The Loop Apartments
review_text: The staff here is always very polite and welcoming. I have found the complex to be very safe. The ladies at the front desk downstairs have been very sweet and helpful. They often have food or tables downstairs where they offer free sweets, clothing and gifts to residents. The security guard and maintenance man are both friendly and easy to talk to. There is a gym upstairs with dumbbells and a few elliptical machines that I rarely use, although the deck on the roof is a nice place to relax or read in the sun. Overall, I have very few complaints about my time here and they are limited to minor appliance malfunctions with the washing machine and dishwasher.
owner_answer: Thank you so much, Austin! We are continuing to be the best for our residents!

name: The Loop Apartments
review_text: Beautiful skydeck that has been renovated and is so vibrant and spacious. Great space to not just hang out but study now that there are umbrellas - a favorite! Elizabeth in the office is always helpful and passionate about The Loop and the residents. This is a great space to live in the Isla Vista market as housing is so limited.
owner_answer: Hello, thank you so much for your review. We appreciate your feedback!

name: The Loop Apartments
review_text:
The loop is unreasonably overpriced and still charges big fees for being a couple days behind payment. Their website is deceiving, the rooms look nothing alike in person. After I got here my room literally looked like a jail cell! The place was empty, with no lights, ugly concrete floors with skid marks (Totally unfurnished). They have NO parking for guests. The roof has a gym with ok dumbells and 2 rusty machines that were probably bought at a yard sale(Lame). The least they could do is put a couple hot tubs up there. They have plenty of space and money for it.

They also have stupid scan cards that occasionally don't work, so I've had to stand outside and wait for a roommate to get me plenty of times. And no one at the front desk ever pickups the phone, so don't even bother calling.

I would NOT recommend this place to anyone. There are plenty of inexpensive, honest, furnished and generally better places in IV and SB. DO NOT settle for this hole!
owner_answer: Ezana, I am sorry to hear this. We want all of our residents to enjoy their living experience at The Loop and I want to ensure that you are one of them. I would love to discuss this with you in person anytime. Please feel free to reach out to me at (805) 328-5007. Thanks Ezana.

name: The Loop Apartments
review_text:
I have lived here for 9 months. I only have one good thing to say about this place: Louise you are the man!. Everything else is pretty awful. Its overpriced, they lie, they are intrusive.

They advertise double rooms as singles. They use a splintery wooden divider that goes 4 feet up to separate their 'rooms'. I didn't learn about this until I moved in because there are no pictures or even mention of this on their website.

The "exclusive rooftop gym" is a few free weights and elliptical. The roof is not exclusive. Tenants aren't allowed to throw parties, however management will rent the roof out to outside parties the majority of weekends. These parties blast loud music throughout the night, often enough to shake the floor of my 3rd floor apartment. Tenants are unable to use the Gym on these days.

The largest issue I have had by far is Privacy here. Every week or so, we will have a 24 hour notice form on our door. Usually tours scheduled for 9AM-10AM. During this time, management will let themselves into your house. They have even opened my roommates bedroom door unannounced, after letting themselves into the apartment at 9AM. These tours  are consistent, and if your apartment is messy they will point it out to you.

Don't let them fool you. They will say "This is the average price of the area" or "Theres nothing else left". Don't listen. Its not.

They also give gift cards when people write reviews. Probably why their rating has stayed so high over the past year. But its going to catch up eventually.
owner_answer: Thank you for the review. The Loop is under new management as of June 2018 and we are starting to make new changes and implement policies and procedures that are best for our residents. We have a brand new team managing the property and are striving to be efficient with resident issues, phone calls and unit walks. Moving forward, there will be a lot of changes that take place to cater to the residents needs and demands. Thank you

review_text: I lived at the Loop for two years and I must say is one of the best places to live in Isla Vista. Really smooth management transition and I must say things changed for the best. Elizabeth and Deshani are extremely helpful and I really enjoy the resident/management relationship!!

name: The Loop Apartments
review_text: I loved living here. I was in one of the least expensive rooms, (still over $900 a month) but my apartment had a great view. From my side of the building you could see the whole mountain range and it looked right onto the street or "the loop" where everyone walks by. It got pretty loud on weekend nights but it was very entertaining to people watch. The management is very responsive and friendly, and the building is very safe since you need a key card to scan in multiple times. The building is modern and fairly updated and the roof is awesome.There are nice laundry rooms on both the 2nd and 3rd floors but they are a bit pricy. There isn't A/C but there isn't anywhere else in isla vista either. Your apartment will come furnished with desks and chairs, twin beds and dressers. The downside of the place is that you will be paying a lot for a small shared space. You can easily find large single rooms in isla vista for less than you would be paying here, however the The Loop is right in the heart of town where all the food and stores are, and you will be a walking distance from all of them which comes in handy. Unless you can afford the parking garage I recommend finding parking on the street. The bus stop is about a ten minute walk from the building which isn't bad.
owner_answer: Thank you Sydney! Great information! We are happy you liked it!

No Courtesy Officer as advertised to manage noise or lobby delivery thefts.  Dirty upon movein TV cables missing.  Harassment inspections & meetings request to coerce & intimidate unenforceable, non expense, frivolous & excessive ($500 per tenant) civil noise fines in attempt to subsidize low occupancy & profit, Misapply our $1,600 pp rents towards & continues to assess excessive daily $10 late fees. name: The Loop Apartments
review_text:
They stole over $4,000 from me and put me in an unfurnished room and still charged me for a furnished room. Also charged me for the pet fee even when I only stayed in that one room divided into 4 "rooms" for 2 days and never brought my dog. Worst apartment ever.

For $1750 per month you'd expect in your "private room" a wall that makes it private from your roommate's room. No lights in the "rooms". To turn on the fan, you need a PIN or PAPERCLIP to press the button. Why? Simply because. Just because. No air-conditioning or ventilation. Which is against the law where I'm from.

Found a place in Santa Barbara for $1200 per month with a much bigger PRIVATE room, great private bathroom, much easier private parking, ALL utilities included and furnished! Keep searching, you'll find a better place that is worth the money! (Try Century Butler Realty in Santa Barbara)

UPDATE: After fighting for a refund, the manager said "You wouldn't bother going through the trouble of a legal battle to get your money back" which I proved otherwise. After filing a lawsuit, the owner contacted me and begged that I drop it if he gives me a full refund for the $4,000 + the $1,750 (pet fee included). Do NOT let them bully you. Someone should report this place.
owner_answer: Levi, we are sorry to hear this!
